JOHANNESBURG - The world of house music has been rocked by the death of international DJ and producer Avicii. He died on Friday at the age of 28. WATCH: #Avicii fans shocked by his untimely death DJ Euphonik says Avicii was a pioneer in the industry and "the best of the best." "He had a unique way of creating melodies," said Euphonik. "He was just the nicest guy in the world. He had massive success, he was humble… [an] overall nice guy." DJ Fresh says Avicii has left a legacy that will continue to inspire future generations. "Right now in SA there are so many kids making incredible music and I think it’s from seeing people like Avicii," said Fresh. "I think his legacy is well cemented. His legacy will live on for another 100 years." eNCA